URL: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7865&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/7865&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;   The `KafkaController::replicasAreValid` method currently returns a&lt;br/&gt;
   boolean indicating if replicas are valid or not. But the failure&lt;br/&gt;
   condition loses any context on why replicas are not valid. This change&lt;br/&gt;
   updates the metod to return the error conition if validation fails. This&lt;br/&gt;
   allows caller to report the error to the client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   The change also renames the `replicasAreValid` method to&lt;br/&gt;
   `validateReplicas` to reflect updated semantics.&lt;/p&gt;

